1
00:00:13,640 --> 00:00:14,119
Hey

2
00:00:14,919 --> 00:00:16,679
Why is the anesthetic I ordered short?

3
00:00:17,440 --> 00:00:19,359
For local anesthesia, I need extra supply.

4
00:00:19,760 --> 00:00:20,920
You have to make up the missing amount.

5
00:00:21,239 --> 00:00:22,079
Or I'll report you.

6
00:00:22,480 --> 00:00:23,960
I wonder how well it works.

7
00:00:24,600 --> 00:00:26,519
If only I had someone to practice on.

8
00:00:35,240 --> 00:00:35,719
You.

9
00:00:59,960 --> 00:01:00,479
What are you doing?

10
00:01:02,600 --> 00:01:03,520
What are you doing? Let go!

11
00:01:05,439 --> 00:01:05,959
Get off!

12
00:01:06,319 --> 00:01:06,840
Get off!

13
00:01:24,519 --> 00:01:26,439
Why can't I reach Zhao Yan?

14
00:01:27,239 --> 00:01:28,439
Hope nothing's happened.

15
00:01:29,879 --> 00:01:30,400
Boss Bai.

16
00:01:30,879 --> 00:01:31,760
Where is this?

17
00:01:32,840 --> 00:01:33,359
This?

18
00:01:33,560 --> 00:01:35,319
This was during our overseas team retreat.

19
00:01:37,560 --> 00:01:39,239
What's this stamp printed on it?

20
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:41,840
It's a popular local thing called

21
00:01:41,840 --> 00:01:43,000
a Nuna stamp.

22
00:01:43,000 --> 00:01:44,599
It's made from plant-based ingredients.

23
00:01:44,599 --> 00:01:45,959
It fades within a few weeks.

24
00:01:46,560 --> 00:01:47,040
Look.

25
00:01:47,200 --> 00:01:48,239
I have one here too.

26
00:01:48,239 --> 00:01:50,519
Yu Tianfang also took everyone to buy stamps.

27
00:01:50,680 --> 00:01:52,480
It's just like those pork stamps.

28
00:01:54,319 --> 00:01:55,439
The people on this retreat,

29
00:01:55,439 --> 00:01:57,280
especially those with the Nuna stamp,

30
00:01:57,560 --> 00:01:58,359
do you have a list?

31
00:01:58,519 --> 00:01:59,280
I'll make one for you.

32
00:02:00,920 --> 00:02:01,319
Xiao Mao.

33
00:02:01,840 --> 00:02:02,480
Come here a sec.

34
00:02:06,560 --> 00:02:07,000
Go.

35
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:08,400
Make a list of everyone who went on

36
00:02:08,400 --> 00:02:08,960
the last overseas retreat for me.

37
00:02:10,199 --> 00:02:11,919
I happen to have the retreat list on my phone.

38
00:02:12,520 --> 00:02:13,159
Let me find it.

39
00:02:20,960 --> 00:02:22,120
You went on the retreat too?

40
00:02:23,879 --> 00:02:24,759
Which one is you?

41
00:02:28,919 --> 00:02:29,360
This one.

42
00:02:29,759 --> 00:02:31,319
Do you know what happened to Cindy?

43
00:02:31,319 --> 00:02:32,360
I heard

44
00:02:32,560 --> 00:02:33,719
Cindy drowned.

45
00:02:34,759 --> 00:02:36,080
Send me the list, then you can go.

46
00:02:39,439 --> 00:02:39,879
By the way,

47
00:02:40,400 --> 00:02:41,199
that list,

48
00:02:41,560 --> 00:02:42,400
send it directly to me.

49
00:02:42,759 --> 00:02:43,719
What's your name?

50
00:02:44,879 --> 00:02:46,000
I'm... I'm Mao Lele.

51
00:02:47,360 --> 00:02:48,240
No need to be nervous.

52
00:02:48,240 --> 00:02:50,039
This is just routine questioning.

53
00:02:50,560 --> 00:02:51,199
Don't worry.

54
00:02:51,560 --> 00:02:52,199
You can go.

55
00:02:55,800 --> 00:02:57,400
Captain Chu, it's so late.

56
00:02:57,400 --> 00:02:58,560
Let's go grab dinner first.

57
00:02:59,280 --> 00:02:59,919
Boss Bai,

58
00:02:59,919 --> 00:03:00,919
dinner can wait.

59
00:03:00,919 --> 00:03:02,319
Everyone on this list,

60
00:03:02,319 --> 00:03:03,759
we need to question them all.

61
00:03:03,759 --> 00:03:04,560
Captain Chu,

62
00:03:04,800 --> 00:03:06,479
we're in a tough spot here.

63
00:03:06,879 --> 00:03:08,400
If you keep investigating like this,

64
00:03:08,400 --> 00:03:10,400
my resort's business will be ruined.

65
00:03:10,400 --> 00:03:11,520
Besides,

66
00:03:11,520 --> 00:03:13,599
you only suspect the killer's hiding here,

67
00:03:13,759 --> 00:03:15,080
you don't have hard evidence, right?

68
00:03:15,280 --> 00:03:16,000
Boss Bai,

69
00:03:16,319 --> 00:03:18,199
we completely understand your situation.

70
00:03:18,199 --> 00:03:20,520
We hope you can understand ours too.

71
00:03:20,520 --> 00:03:21,639
This is our job.

72
00:03:21,639 --> 00:03:23,319
Until we catch the suspect,

73
00:03:23,319 --> 00:03:25,199
we're responsible for everyone's safety.

74
00:03:27,560 --> 00:03:29,039
The guest rooms have been searched.

75
00:03:29,719 --> 00:03:31,360
The surveillance room won't be fixed anytime soon.

76
00:03:31,759 --> 00:03:32,560
Hiding here

77
00:03:32,919 --> 00:03:33,840
should be safe enough.

78
00:03:34,360 --> 00:03:35,840
But even the cops can't find the suspect.

79
00:03:35,840 --> 00:03:37,080
Who am I supposed to investigate?

80
00:03:37,719 --> 00:03:38,520
The more I think about it,

81
00:03:39,240 --> 00:03:41,319
the most suspicious person is me.

82
00:03:58,680 --> 00:03:59,360
Hello.

83
00:04:02,400 --> 00:04:03,080
Hello,

84
00:04:03,879 --> 00:04:04,560
ma'am.

85
00:04:36,959 --> 00:04:37,399
Up there!

86
00:04:37,519 --> 00:04:38,000
After him!

87
00:04:42,839 --> 00:04:43,759
Tianfang, what's wrong?

88
00:04:43,759 --> 00:04:44,279
Run!

89
00:04:44,519 --> 00:04:45,279
Something's happened again.

90
00:04:46,639 --> 00:04:47,600
Freeze! Don't move!

91
00:04:48,199 --> 00:04:48,759
Police!

92
00:04:49,519 --> 00:04:50,839
Step back! Protect the crime scene!

93
00:04:53,480 --> 00:04:53,920
How is she?

94
00:04:54,199 --> 00:04:54,920
She still has a pulse.

95
00:04:56,959 --> 00:04:57,720
Call an ambulance!

96
00:04:58,360 --> 00:04:59,000
HQ, come in, HQ.

97
00:04:59,360 --> 00:05:01,399
A woman was attacked at Qingyuan Resort.

98
00:05:01,399 --> 00:05:02,279
We need backup.

99
00:05:02,879 --> 00:05:04,120
Isn't this Fenni?

100
00:05:04,120 --> 00:05:04,600
What happened?

101
00:05:04,879 --> 00:05:05,600
What's going on here?

102
00:05:10,639 --> 00:05:11,360
Come take a look at this.

103
00:05:12,199 --> 00:05:13,000
This footprint...

104
00:05:13,319 --> 00:05:14,399
It's identical to the one we saw

105
00:05:14,399 --> 00:05:15,480
outside the surveillance room.

106
00:05:15,879 --> 00:05:16,279
Captain Chu.

107
00:05:16,519 --> 00:05:16,959
Look at this.

108
00:05:21,759 --> 00:05:22,480
Maomao,

109
00:05:23,040 --> 00:05:24,639
you really saved my life back there.

110
00:05:25,480 --> 00:05:25,959
Bro,

111
00:05:26,879 --> 00:05:28,519
you're always the one helping me.

112
00:05:28,519 --> 00:05:30,519
This is just a small favor in return.

113
00:05:31,480 --> 00:05:32,240
Right now,

114
00:05:32,240 --> 00:05:34,240
I'm a suspect in the cops' eyes.

115
00:05:34,240 --> 00:05:35,439
You aren't afraid of getting dragged in,

116
00:05:35,439 --> 00:05:36,439
and you still help me out like this.

117
00:05:36,759 --> 00:05:38,399
I'm seriously touched.

118
00:05:39,079 --> 00:05:41,240
Why am I so damn unlucky?

119
00:05:41,240 --> 00:05:41,839
Bro,

120
00:05:42,319 --> 00:05:44,920
the Cindy situation isn't even over,

121
00:05:44,920 --> 00:05:46,680
and now Fenni too.

122
00:05:48,800 --> 00:05:50,600
I haven't even eaten yet.

123
00:05:52,160 --> 00:05:52,560
Bro,

124
00:05:52,839 --> 00:05:53,439
there's bread.

125
00:05:59,600 --> 00:06:00,680
Bro, slow down.

126
00:06:01,399 --> 00:06:02,839
A can of beer would be perfect right now.

127
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:06,959
Bro, here's a cola.

128
00:06:08,519 --> 00:06:09,079
That'll do.

129
00:06:21,160 --> 00:06:22,720
Look at that thing on her face.

130
00:06:23,040 --> 00:06:25,600
Anyone can come looking for work at this resort, huh.

131
00:06:25,920 --> 00:06:28,000
Zhao Yan was just staring at her.

132
00:06:28,279 --> 00:06:28,920
And he said,

133
00:06:29,240 --> 00:06:30,120
"if there's a chance later."

134
00:06:31,279 --> 00:06:31,959
A chance for what?

135
00:06:32,560 --> 00:06:33,519
You know, that kind of thing.

136
00:06:34,720 --> 00:06:35,279
Hey, miss.

137
00:06:36,759 --> 00:06:37,360
Miss.

138
00:06:38,160 --> 00:06:38,959
Are you all right?

139
00:06:39,680 --> 00:06:40,879
So damn stupid.

140
00:06:42,839 --> 00:06:43,560
What are you staring at?

141
00:06:44,279 --> 00:06:45,079
What are you looking at?

142
00:06:45,480 --> 00:06:47,079
What are you doing out here during work hours?

143
00:06:47,279 --> 00:06:48,199
If you don't get back, I'm telling you,

144
00:06:48,199 --> 00:06:49,240
I'll dock your pay.

145
00:06:50,839 --> 00:06:51,680
You two, get back to work.

146
00:06:53,920 --> 00:06:54,439
Miss.

147
00:06:55,399 --> 00:06:56,439
Looking like this,

148
00:06:56,800 --> 00:06:57,639
how can you go back?

149
00:06:57,639 --> 00:06:58,639
Come inside with me first.

150
00:06:58,639 --> 00:06:59,959
And change into some clean clothes.

151
00:07:00,120 --> 00:07:00,560
From now on,

152
00:07:01,079 --> 00:07:01,920
you'll work here.

153
00:07:05,160 --> 00:07:05,800
Come on.

154
00:07:10,639 --> 00:07:12,000
I mean, seriously, you two,

155
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:13,319
do my words mean nothing to you?

156
00:07:13,600 --> 00:07:14,720
I told you to go back.

157
00:07:14,720 --> 00:07:16,199
Yet you're still here mocking her.

158
00:07:16,360 --> 00:07:17,319
Why don't you look in the mirror

159
00:07:17,319 --> 00:07:18,319
and see what you look like?

160
00:07:18,560 --> 00:07:20,399
One's a snake, the other's a crab,

161
00:07:20,560 --> 00:07:21,399
and you have the nerve to laugh.

162
00:07:21,680 --> 00:07:21,959
Move it.

163
00:07:21,959 --> 00:07:22,720
Yu Tianfang, you...

164
00:07:26,879 --> 00:07:27,319
Bro,

165
00:07:28,199 --> 00:07:29,360
If it weren't for you,

166
00:07:30,399 --> 00:07:32,000
I wouldn't have the courage to keep living.

167
00:07:33,120 --> 00:07:34,560
How many times have I told you?

168
00:07:34,759 --> 00:07:36,480
Stop saying such depressing things.

169
00:07:36,480 --> 00:07:37,759
You've got to have more confidence.

170
00:07:38,120 --> 00:07:39,639
Cindy and Fenni,

171
00:07:39,959 --> 00:07:41,120
they're gorgeous, right?

172
00:07:41,639 --> 00:07:43,079
They still ended up getting hurt.

173
00:07:43,240 --> 00:07:43,800
Bro,

174
00:07:44,319 --> 00:07:45,720
I believe you're not the killer.

175
00:07:46,120 --> 00:07:47,839
If only the police believed that too.

176
00:07:48,600 --> 00:07:49,319
Right now,

177
00:07:49,600 --> 00:07:50,800
I just hope Fenni is okay,

178
00:07:51,079 --> 00:07:52,160
and that they can save her.

179
00:07:52,680 --> 00:07:53,079
That way,

180
00:07:53,680 --> 00:07:55,920
she can name the real killer.

181
00:08:03,600 --> 00:08:04,720
Got anything else to eat?

182
00:08:05,360 --> 00:08:05,959
I'm still hungry.

183
00:08:07,279 --> 00:08:07,680
What's this?

184
00:08:09,319 --> 00:08:09,920
Cosmetic injections.

185
00:08:10,319 --> 00:08:10,720
Bro,

186
00:08:11,079 --> 00:08:12,120
I'll go find you something to eat.

187
00:08:12,319 --> 00:08:13,000
Stay put.

188
00:08:13,000 --> 00:08:13,879
Just wait here for me.

189
00:08:20,360 --> 00:08:20,920
Captain Chu.

190
00:08:21,360 --> 00:08:22,519
We've looked into everyone,

191
00:08:23,079 --> 00:08:24,199
and there are no leads.

192
00:08:25,240 --> 00:08:26,079
It seems like someone here

193
00:08:26,079 --> 00:08:27,480
is deliberately hiding information.

194
00:08:28,560 --> 00:08:29,240
Don't lose heart.

195
00:08:30,199 --> 00:08:31,639
We haven't come up empty.

196
00:08:32,159 --> 00:08:33,240
At least we now know

197
00:08:33,240 --> 00:08:34,919
Cindy and Fenni's social connections.

198
00:08:35,200 --> 00:08:36,080
We also know

199
00:08:36,200 --> 00:08:38,240
neither of them got along with anyone.

200
00:08:39,080 --> 00:08:40,840
But doesn't that make it harder to investigate?

201
00:08:41,559 --> 00:08:42,840
You're pretty optimistic.

202
00:08:45,799 --> 00:08:47,080
I learned it from my mentor.

203
00:08:48,279 --> 00:08:49,279
When my dad passed away,

204
00:08:49,679 --> 00:08:50,960
you were still a rookie on the force,

205
00:08:51,639 --> 00:08:52,799
and I was still in grad school.

206
00:08:53,279 --> 00:08:53,960
In the blink of an eye,

207
00:08:54,320 --> 00:08:55,240
so much time has passed.

208
00:08:56,919 --> 00:08:58,279
Whenever something like this came up,

209
00:08:58,799 --> 00:09:00,120
my mentor would tell me,

210
00:09:01,720 --> 00:09:02,879
"Don't always think about winning.

211
00:09:03,639 --> 00:09:05,159
Focus on the path right in front of you."

212
00:09:39,200 --> 00:09:39,679
Hello.

213
00:09:40,240 --> 00:09:41,240
The password is still wrong.

214
00:09:41,759 --> 00:09:43,720
She seems to change it regularly.

215
00:09:43,720 --> 00:09:45,000
I can't find a pattern yet.

216
00:09:45,320 --> 00:09:47,279
Only by getting the files inside

217
00:09:47,799 --> 00:09:50,080
will we have a chance at real freedom.

218
00:09:50,360 --> 00:09:51,720
I'll be waiting for good news.

219
00:09:52,039 --> 00:09:52,720
Don't worry.

220
00:09:53,039 --> 00:09:54,080
I won't give up.

221
00:09:55,039 --> 00:09:55,879
She owes me,

222
00:09:56,440 --> 00:09:57,879
and I'll make her pay it all back at once.

